## 4. Godot 4 Implementation Notes

### 4.1 Project Structure
```text
res://
├── Scenes/
│   ├── Main.tscn (Level & Spawner)
│   ├── Player.tscn (CharacterBody2D)
│   ├── Weapon.tscn (Node2D with Sprite & Logic)
│   ├── AmmoPickup.tscn (Area2D)
│   ├── Flag.tscn (StaticBody2D)
│   └── UI.tscn (CanvasLayer)
├── Scripts/
│   ├── Player.gd
│   ├── Weapon.gd
│   ├── GameManager.gd
│   └── NetworkManager.gd
└── Assets/
```

### 4.2 Key Technical Solutions
*   **Multiplayer:** Use `MultiplayerSpawner` for the House and Flags. Use `MultiplayerSynchronizer` on Player `CharacterBody2D` and `Weapon` variables to sync Ammo counts without manual RPCs.
*   **Ammo Pickup Signal:**
    ```gdscript
    # AmmoPickup.gd
    func _on_area_entered(area):
        if area.is_in_group("player"):
            # Fix BUG-02 here if testing students
            area.heal_ammo(6) 
            queue_free()
    ```
*   **Movement Fix:**
    ```gdscript
    # Player.gd (CharacterBody2D)
    func get_input():
        var input_dir = Input.get_vector("ui_left", "ui_right", "ui_up", "ui_down")
        velocity = input_dir * speed
    ```
*   **Collision Shape Fix:** Ensure all `Area2D` nodes have a `CollisionShape2D` child with a `RectangleShape2D` or `CapsuleShape2D` assigned. **Empty shapes cause silent failures.**

